<section id="Changing_Report_Views" remap="TID_15453">
	<title>Changing Report Views</title>
	<para>
		Some reports can be viewed as charts as well as lists. Note that this will depend on the type of data and on how the report has been created. Where applicable, you will see these additional buttons.
	</para>
	<procedure>
		<title>To Change the View of a Report</title>
		<step>
			<para>
				Navigate to <menuchoice><guimenu>Cloud Intelligence</guimenu><guisubmenu>Reports</guisubmenu></menuchoice>.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click the report to view. Click one of the following buttons for the view you want.
			</para>
			<itemizedlist>
				<listitem>
					<para>
						Click 
						<inlinemediaobject>
							<imageobject>
								<imagedata fileref="images/2284.png" />
							</imageobject>
						</inlinemediaobject>for Graph View.
					</para>
				</listitem>
				<listitem>
					<para>
						Click 
						<inlinemediaobject>
							<imageobject>
								<imagedata fileref="images/2285.png" />
							</imageobject>
						</inlinemediaobject>for Hybrid View.
					</para>
				</listitem>
				<listitem>
					<para>
						Click 
						<inlinemediaobject>
							<imageobject>
								<imagedata fileref="images/2022.png" />
							</imageobject>
						</inlinemediaobject>for Tabular View.
					</para>
				</listitem>
			</itemizedlist>
		</step>
	</procedure>
</section>